perimentation and a walk through the coffee plantation.</p><p>Afterwards you will be free to explore the local area, taking in the scenery and relaxing.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Coffee plantation tour</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>7</day1><day2>7</day2><destfrom>Medellín</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>This morning you will transfer north to Medell&amp;#237;n, the second largest city in Colombia. Known for having year round pleasant weather, the city is also called The City of Eternal Spring. After arrival and check in you will have a free afternoon to start enjoying the sights.</p><p>Medell&amp;#237;n has transformed into a tourist destination and offers various activities and sights for different tastes. Spend time wandering Plaza Botero, where you will see some of his sculptures as well as performers and artists at work.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>8</day1><day2>8</day2><destfrom>Medellín Transformation Tour</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>This morning you will be collected for a Medell&amp;#237;n city tour, where you will learn all about its transformation over the recent years. A mere 20 years ago, Medell&amp;#237;n was considered one of the most dangerous cities in the world. During the reign of Pablo Escobar, Medell&amp;#237;n was purely known for his drug cartel. In the years after his death, the transformation of Medell&amp;#237;n began as politicians starting investing heavily in infrastructure and wanted eagerly to change the worlds perception of the city. The tour will cover everything from history to present day, and be sure to leave you knowing Colombia a little better!</p><p>The rest of the day will be at your leisure.</p></description><accommodation>1 n