&amp;#39;s plazas, cobbled streets and teach you all about the vast history of this fascinating city. You will visit various churches and galleries, as well as the UNESCO World Heritage Site of Castillo de San Felipe de Barajas, which was built during the colonial period to protect the Spanish from invasion by the French and English. Enjoy the rich culture of each site you visit and after the tour has finished you are free for the remainder of the day.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Cartagena City Tour</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>12</day1><day2>12</day2><destfrom>Cartagena</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today you are free to enjoy Cartagena and all it has to offer. Some of our suggestions are below:</p><p>&amp;#9679; Take a trip to the traditional fishing village of La Boquilla where you can enjoy a canoe ride through mangroves and the lagoon.</p><p>&amp;#9679; Visit a volcano where you can jump inside the crater and enjoy a natural mud bath. The minerals are considered to help rejuvenate the skin, you can then take a dip in the lake to wash the mud away.</p><p>&amp;#9679; Spend the day on the Rosario Islands, where you can explore the national park, swim in the warm Caribbean waters or relax on the beach.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>13</day1><day2>13</day2><destfrom>Cartagena</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today you will be transferred to the airport for your flight to Quito. Upon arrival check in to your accommodation and enjoy the remainder of the day.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>14</day1><day2>14</day2><destfrom>Quito City Tour</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Explore the highlights of Quito and visit the Middle of the World on a city tour. You will be collected from your hotel and start by visiting the downtown area, one of the biggest in South America. You will visit the oldest street in Quito, La Ronda, which was once home to poets, musicians and politicians. Your local guide will take you to a local eatery where you will have a lesson in the local spices that are used in traditional Ecuadorian food.</p><p>After exploring La Ronda you will visit the Independence Square and the historical buildings that surround it; the Cathedral, Presidential Palace, El Sagrario Church and La Compania de Jesus which is one of the most beautiful baroque churches in South America. After this you will drive to the viewpoint at Panecillo Hill where you can experience some incredible views of the city and surroundings.</p><p>Finally, you will drive north of Quito for 30km to the equator that divides the northern and southern hemispheres. You will visit the monument built to honour the French Expedition that arrived in Ecuador and determined the correct equator line, as well as explore the scientific and cultural museum.</p><p>After a packed day you will return to Quito where you can relax and unwind for the evening.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Quito Middle of the World &amp; City Tour</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>15</day1><day2>15</day2><destfrom>Quito City</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today you will have a unique adventure to the Mindo Cloud Forest, an ecological paradise located around 2 hours drive northwest of Quito. Learn about the great diversity of the animals and plants that live here and enjoy the scenery. You will also visit a beautiful orchid garden before heading back to Quito.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>16</day1><day2>16</day2><destfrom>Riobamba &amp; Cotopaxi National Park</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>You will be transferred to Cotopaxi National Park where you will have a guided visit of the park. Along the way you will drive along the Pan-American highway which is known as &amp;#34;The Volcano Avenue&amp;#34; and you will soon witness the world?s highest active volcano - Cotopaxi.</p><p>You will drive through the park, admiring the spectacular views and if weather conditions allow take a short hike through the lush landscape. The journey continues as you visit a local indigenous market to wander and pick up some souvenirs. You will then arrive in Riobamba where you will have a free evening to relax.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Visit Cotopaxi National Park</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>17</day1><day2>17</day2><destfrom>Cuenca &amp; The Devil's Nose Train</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today you will be collected for the Devil&amp;#39;s Nose train expedition. After an early breakfast, you will head for the town of Alausi. This is the base for your exhilarating train journey. Known as &amp;#34;the most difficult railway in the world&amp;#34; your descent will go from 2346 metres to 1860 meters in a mere 30 minutes, as you zig zag through the landscape and marvel at this engineering feat.</p><p>After the train journey your guide will bring you to the Tolte?s community where you will enjoy lunch along with a traditional dance show. In the afternoon you are free to choose from a range of options. These include:</p><p>&amp;#9679; Hike up 330 stairs to an incredible viewpoint and the perfect place to see the Devil?s train network from further away</p><p>&amp;#9679; Horseback riding</p><p>&amp;#9679; A biking tour through the surrounding area and communities</p><p>&amp;#9679; Visit a local organic farm to see how they are developing agro-tourism</p><p>Later on you will be transferred to your accommodation in Cuenco and have a free evening.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Devil's Nose Train Journey</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>18</day1><day2>18</day2><destfrom>Cuenca City Tour</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today you&amp;#39;ll enjoy a city tour of Cuenca. After breakfast you will visit the city&amp;#39;s historic centre as well as a traditional neighbourhood of Cuenca. Highlights include the San Sebastian church, modern art museum, the flower plaza, the Cathedral of the Immaculate Conception and finally the Hat Factory, also known as El Paja Toquilla.</p><p>Your tour will finish at a scenic viewpoint where you can witness the majestic mountains providing a picturesque backdrop to charming red roofs and church domes.</p><p>You?ll have the rest of the day free to explore Cuenca.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Cuenca City Tour</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>19</day1><day2>19</day2><destfrom>Guayaquil</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Enjoy breakfast before you are collected and taken a mere 30 minutes away to El Cajas National Park. This stunning area consists of over 200 lagoons and is a vital water source for Cuenca and Ecuador as a whole. You?ll walk for around 45 minutes to reach the highest part of the park, which sits at 4,000 metres. The surrounding scenery is beautiful and you might even see some of the many animals that call it home, from the South American condors to the allusive puma.</p><p>You will then walk for around three hours to reach the Toreadora Lagoon, before finally driving onto Guayaquil City.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>20</day1><day2>20</day2><destfrom>Galapagos Islands</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>This morning you will be transferred to the airport to board your flight to San Cristobel in the Galapagos Islands. You will be met by your guide who will transfer you to your cruise for the duration of the trip. After introductions and check in you will then visit the Interpretation Centre and Frigate Bird Hill. At the centre you will begin to learn about the Galapagos Islands and it&amp;#39;s eco-logical significance, as well as the conservation efforts that the local authorities are undertaking. Your group will then hike to the Frigate Bird Hill where you witness both species of the frigate bird as well as take in the beautiful view of the surrounding bay.</p></description><accommodation>1  . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s), 1 Lunch(es)</meals><includedexcursions>Galapagos Cruise &amp; Activities</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>21</day1><day2>21</day2><destfrom>Galapagos Islands</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>This morning we head to the shores of San Cristobel. Walk amongst the frolicing sea lions, snorkel, or take a walk to a hidden lagoon where you might spot black necked stilts or white cheeked pintails.</p><p>After lunch we will spend the afternoon visiting Punta Pitt &amp; Islet on San Cristobal Island. You will then do a little hiking to the only spot on the island where you can see all the booby species in the same place. The views from here are incredible! You will also have time to snorkel or kayak, admiring the scenery from a different perspective.</p><p>Enjoy a relaxing evening on the boat with dinner and socialising with your group.</p></description><accommodation>1  . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s), 1 Lunch(es), 1 Dinner(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Galapagos Cruise &amp; Activities</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>22</day1><day2>22</day2><destfrom>Galapagos Islands</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>This morning you have a dry landing on Espa&amp;#241;ola Island (Suarez Point). Enjoy a guided walk across the lava terrain and hike cross the inactive lava fields. Besides the sea lion colonies, this is one of the most important sites for bird watching. Many species, like the hooded mockingbird and red-billed tropic can be spotted and observed closely. Past the nesting grounds you&amp;#39;ll reach the world&amp;#39;s largest colony of waved albatross. From May to December their mating rituals are a highlight of the visit. Later you will visit the famous blowhole, where water shoots about 23m (75ft) high.</p><p>After lunch on board you will navigate to the white beach at Gardner Bay. Snorkel in the azure-waters which are home to schools of brightly coloured tropical fish and the Pacific green turtle. Friendly sea lions may also join you snorkelling here too! You will then make a wet landing onto the wide sand beach. It a home to a large sea lion colony, enjoy marvelling at these playful creatures as you stroll along the sand.</p></description><accommodation>1  . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s), 1 Lunch(es), 1 Dinner(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Galapagos Cruise &amp; Activities</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>23</day1><day2>23</day2><destfrom>Galapagos Islands</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Floreana Island has had a colourful history: Pirates, whalers, convicts, and a small band of somewhat peculiar colonists - a Baroness among them - who chose a Robinson Crusoe existence that ended in mystery and death. Today roughly fifty Ecuadorians inhabit the island. Punta Cormorant offers two highly contrasting beaches; the strand where the yacht anchors is composed of volcanic olivine crystals, giving it a greenish tint that glitters in the sun. From here the trail crosses the neck of the isthmus - which rises to form a cinder cone - to a beach of very fine white sand, formed by the erosion of coral skeletons. Between the two beaches is a salt lagoon frequented by flamingos, pintails, stilts and other wading birds.</p><p>After breakfast, the dinghy will take you to the rocky crevice of Devil's Crown where you have the opportunity to do some deep-water snorkelling off Floreana Island. Later you will make a wet landing at the beach of Cormorant Point. Hike along the sandy beach and keep your eyes out for the American Flamingo lagoon.</p><p>This afternoon you will visit Post Office Bay and Baroness Lookout where you can admire the spectacular views. Post Office Bay has a working post office, so make sure you bring your postcards to send your friends and family back home! From Baroness Lookout you will be rewarded with spectacular panoramic views of the Galapagos Islands.</p></description><accommodation>1  . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s), 1 Lunch(es), 1 Dinner(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Galapagos Cruise &amp; Activities</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>24</day1><day2>24</day2><destfrom>Galapagos Islands</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>This morning you will have a wet landing at Barrington Bay, the beach of Santa Fe. This island is home to a huge amount of wildlife, endemic to the Galapagos Islands. One of the most unique species is the rare Barrington land iguana although it is not as easy to spot as some of the other land iguanas on South Plaza island. You will also see a large cacti forest and visit a large sea lion colony living on the beach.</p><p>You have the chance to do some snorkelling accompanied by the harmless white tip reef sharks and maybe a sea lion or two!</p><p>This afternoon you will land at South Plaza, one of the most popular islands in the Galapagos archipelago. There are several large sea lion colonies as well as the colourful land iguana. You will take a guided nature walk along the cliff faces, keeping an eye out for the red-billed tropicbird.</p></description><accommodation>1  . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s), 1 Lunch(es), 1 Dinner(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Galapagos Cruise &amp; Activities</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>25</day1><day2>25</day2><destfrom>Galapagos Islands</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>North Seymour is one of the most visited islands of the Galapagos, and is the home for extensive colonies of frigate birds and boobies. You will take an early morning walk around these bird colonies before returning to the boat for a breakfast buffet. This afternoon you will sail to Bachas Beach where you will make a wet landing. You will visit a lagoon, home to various birds including the American flamingo. You may also see the nest holes of the Pacific green turtles who hatch between November and February.</p></description><accommodation>1  . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s), 1 Lunch(es), 1 Dinner(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Galapagos Cruise &amp; Activities</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>26</day1><day2>26</day2><destfrom>Galapagos Islands</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>This morning you will have your last excursion on the Galapagos Islands. You will visit Mosquera, home to the largest concentration of sea lions in the entire archipelago Take a beach walk strolling freely amongst the wildlife, you may even see the strikingly orange Sally Lightfoot Crabs.</p><p>Later you will be assisted by your guide and taken on the dinghy to Baltra where you will transfer to the airport. Fly back to Quito where you will be transferred to your hotel for your last night.</p></description><accommodation>1  . No single room upgrade availabl