 was founded by the Spanish Francisco Pizarro in 1535 as the capital of the new Spanish empire.</p><p>You will visit Huaca Pucllana, an adobe and clay pyramid built around 500 A.D. before taking in the colonial buildings of the historic centre. It is then on to the metropolitan financial district of San Isidro and the commercial centre built on the cliffs of Miraflores offering panoramic views to the Pacific.</p><p>The remainder of the day is at your leisure.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Lima City Tour</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>30</day1><day2>30</day2><destfrom>Nazca Lines</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today you will be collected and transferred from Lima for your Nazca Lines excursion. Fly over the fascinating shapes and learn about the myths and legends that surround them. Following this you will visit Huacachina Desert oasis.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Flight over Nazca Lines &amp; Visit Haucachina Oasis</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>31</day1><day2>31</day2><destfrom>Lima</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today is free for you to relax and recharge or explore more of the sights of Lima.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>32</day1><day2>32</day2><destfrom>Amazon Jungle</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>This morning you will fly into Puerto Maldonado for the start of your Amazon Jungle adventure. You will have the chance to visit the Butterfly House before heading to the port to take a short boat ride to your lodge. After a short briefing about the next days ahead, settle into your cabana and enjoy lunch. Your guide will explain the various excursions and walks that you can take during your time here.</p><p>We recommend taking a walk along the trail system where you will discover the Amazon Basin. It offers a great starting point to immersing yourself in the jungle, with exotic plants surrounding you and various birds soaring above.</p><p>Tonight we recommend taking the Twilight River excursion, where you can witness the environment change before your eyes as the sun goes down. Discover animals of the nocturnal world and learn all about their habits. Return for dinner and enjoy the evening at your leisure.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in a jungle lodge . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s), 1 Lunch(es), 1 Dinner(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Amazon Jungle Excursion &amp; Activities</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>33</day1><day2>33</day2><destfrom>Amazon Jungle</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Awaken to the sounds of the jungle and get ready for another day of adventure. This morning you have the opportunity to visit Lake Sandoval where you can cruise along in wooden canoes, keeping an eye out for the giant river otters that call it home. Other animals you are likely to spot are the howler monkeys, macaws, anacondas, turtles and black caiman. Return to the lodge for lunch.</p><p>This afternoon you could walk the Inkaterra Canopy Walkway, towering above the rainforest floor. For the first quarter of a mile you will walk through the rainforest on a suspension bridge which links eight different platforms - all with incredible jungle views. Spot colourful toucans, woodpeckers, monkeys and sloths.</p><p>Return to the lodge for dinner and an evening at your leisure.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in a jungle lodge . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s), 1 Lunch(es), 1 Dinner(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Amazon Jungle Excursion &amp; Activities</includedexcursions></itine