 Cathedral and the Koricancha Sun Temple, which is believed to have been built in 1200AD.</p><p>You will then visit the archeological Park of Sacsayhuaman, which covers an area of over 3000 hectares and displays wonderful examples of Inca architecture. You will then visit the other archeological sites of Kenko, Puca Pucara and Tambomachay.</p><p>Returning to Cusco, you will have a free evening to relax and soak up the atmosphere. Grab a drink in the Plaza de Armas and enjoy the Cusco lifestyle.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Cusco City Tour</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>37</day1><day2>37</day2><destfrom>Sacred Valley Tour</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>After being collected this morning you will enjoy a tour of the Sacred Valley of the Incas. Your guide will explain the history, myths and legends of the region as you walk between the ruins. You will visit the Inca citadel of Pisac and then explore a typical market of the same name. The colourful market is a wonderful place to pick up some souvenirs.</p><p>Next, you will travel along the Vilcanota River eventually arriving to the city of Urubamba where you will enjoy lunch. Visit the Fortress and Citadel of Ollantaytambo, constructed to guard the entrance to this section of the valley.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Sacred Valley of the Incas Guided Tour</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>38</day1><day2>38</day2><destfrom>Sacred Valley Tour</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today you are free to explore more of the Sacred Valley.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>39</day1><day2>39</day2><destfrom>Aguas Calientes</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today you will transfer to Ollantaytambo where you will get the train to Aguas Calientes, the closest town to Machu Picchu. Travelling by the VistaDome panoramic train, you will experience views of the lush landscape along the way.</p><p>You will have the evening to relax at your accommodation.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s), 1 Dinner(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Ride the VistaDome Train</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>40</day1><day2>40</day2><destfrom>Machu Picchu</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today you will be taken on a guided tour of Machu Picchu before having free time to explore the site at your leisure.</p><p>The Lost City of Machu Picchu was originally completely self-contained, surrounded by agricultural terraces sufficient to feed the population, and watered by natural springs. Located high above the fast flowing Urubamba River, the cloud shrouded ruins have palaces, baths, temples, storage rooms and some 150 houses, all in a remarkable state of preservation that will simply take your breath away.</p><p>The ruins were only discovered by the outside world in 1911, when American explorer Hiram Bingham found them while looking for another &amp;#34;lost city&amp;#34; called Vilcabamba. Due to their isolation many of the buildings are still quite intact and you can't help but admire Huayna Picchu (Young Mountain), which towers above the ruins.</p><p>You will return to your accommodation in Aguas Calientes for a free evening.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Machu Picchu Entrance and Guided Tour</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>41</day1><day2>41</day2><destfrom>Cusco</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>This morning you will board the VistaDome train again and return to Ollantaytambo. From here you will be taken on a tour of the Maras, Moray and Salieneras, where you will visit a colonial town, Inca terraces and salt mines. Moray is a unique archeological site in Peru with several circular depressions in the ground, all layered into the landscape. It&amp;#39;s a truly fascinating area and great for photographs! The village of Maras is famous for its salt evaporation ponds, which are said to have been utilized since the Inca period. The mirage of the salt ponds is a unique image and the only one found in the area.</p><p>After the tour you will be transferred back to Cusco.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>42</day1><day2>42</day2><destfrom>Cusco</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today is free to enjoy Cusco or spend some time relaxing after a packed few days.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>43</day1><day2>43</day2><destfrom>Arequipa</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>You will be taken to the airport for your flight to Arequipa where you will spend the next three nights.</p><p>Arequipa is a lovely colonial era town in Peru, framed by three volcanoes. It is known for its buildings constructed from white volcanic stone, making it a beautiful place to walk around.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>44</day1><day2>44</day2><destfrom>Arequipa</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today you&amp;#39;ll enjoy a city tour of Arequipa and the Santa Catalina Convent, which was closed to the public for almost 400 years after once being home to the nuns of the Dominican Second Order. It is now open to the public and offers lovely gardens and alleyways to stroll through. The monastery was founded in 1579 and remains one of the most important religious sites in Peru.</p><p>Next you will visit the Saint Ignacio Compania, a wonderful example of baroque architecture. While the church dates back to the 1500&amp;#39;s, it has been rebuilt numerous times due to earthquakes.</p><p>Returning to your vehicle you will continue onto the Yanahuara district - most known for its popular viewpoint of the city and surrounding landscape.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Arequipa City Tour</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>45</day1><day2>45</day2><destfrom>Arequipa</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today is a free day in Arequipa to enjoy the city.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>46</day1><day2>46</day2><destfrom>Colca Canyon</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today you will continue the adventure as you head towards Colca Canyon through the high Andean plateau. The four hour journey will take you across some stunning landscape as you drive past glaciers, lakes, volcanoes and mountains. Keep your eyes peeled for some of the many animals that roam in the area, including alpacas, llamas, flamingos, ibis and the Andean eagle. Your driver will stop at various points if a photo opportunity presents itself.</p><p>You will continue to the town of Chivay where you will have a free afternoon. Enjoy the hot thermal springs of La Calera or set off on a short trek, taking in the panoramic view of the canyon.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>47</day1><day2>47</day2><destfrom>Colca Canyon</destfrom><destto></de