, including Uros and Taquile Island.</p><p>Hop on the boat and start the adventure as you first sail to the Uros Islands. It is believed that the Uros were one of the first ethnic groups to populate the Andean region and in the early 60?s starting using the reeds to build artificial islands. You will then continue onto Taquile Island.</p><p>Taquile Island is home to a Quechua population of around 2000 people who are farmers, fishermen and renowned weavers. You will walk for around one hour to reach the main village, as your guide will explain all about life on the island and the history of its people. You will enjoy lunch at a local restaurant of fresh produce before making your way back to the boat.</p><p>You&amp;#39;ll have the remainder of the day to enjoy at your leisure in Puno.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>51</day1><day2>51</day2><destfrom>La Paz</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>This morning you will be collected for an ancient culture tour before arriving to La Paz later on in the day. Visit the Church of the Virgin Morena and a local market, before enjoying lunch by Lake Titicaca. You will then board a speedboat that will take you out to the Sun Island, where you will visit an Inca garden, sacred Inca steps and a beautiful fountain. Another highlight is Pilko Kaina Palace, thought to be built by the Incan emperor Tupac Inca Yupanqui.</p><p>You will return to Copacabana on the boat before hopping in a vehicle to continue onto La Paz. La Paz is the highest capital city in the world and has a stunning mountainous backdrop.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>52</day1><day2>52</day2><destfrom>La Paz City Tour</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>You will be collected for a city tour of La Paz. Your tour begins by exploring the mystical Witches&amp;#39; Market that sells a variety of strange objects such as dried llama foetus. Your guide will explain the culture and history of the market as you wander through, trying to decipher the weird and wonderful things on offer! Next you will visit the San Francisco Church, built between the sixteenth and eighteenth centuries. Other highlights include the Legislative Palace, the Metropolitan Cathedral and finally the Killi Killi viewpoint that offers some of the best views of La Paz.</p><p>You will return to your hotel and the remainder of the day is free at your leisure.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>La Paz City Tour</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>53</day1><day2>53</day2><destfrom>La Paz</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Enjoy free time in La Paz. Speak to your Tailormade Specialist about various excursions that are on offer or take today to recharge and relax and explore at your own pace.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>54</day1><day2>54</day2><destfrom>Salt Flats</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>You will be transferred to the airport and fly to the town of Uyuni, gateway to the Uyuni Salt Flats. The Uyuni Salt Flats are one of the most popular attractions of Bolivia and offer a truly unique landscape that is perfect for keen photographers.</p><p>Upon arrival you will be transferred to your accommodation in the city. You will then enjoy your first day exploring the surrounding area, starting with a visit to the train cemetery. Here you can see the remains of 19th and early 20th century steam locomotives that used to transport salt and minerals. Next up you will visit the town of Coquesa, where the famous mummies dating back from 700 BC are almost perfectly preserved, with skin, hair and nails in tact. Continuing on to the viewpoint of Tunupa volcano, you will observe flamingos in the wetlands.</p><p>Enjoy lunch in the middle of the salt flats (dry season only) before visiting the Salt Museum (which is of course built from salt), followed by a visit to Incahuasi Islands. Here you can see giant cactus, some of them more than 100 years old. The island also offers great views of the salt flats.</p><p>Continue to your accommodation for the evening, a unique salt hotel in the National Park.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Salt Flats Excursion</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>55</day1><day2>55</day2><destfrom>Salt Flats</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>After breakfast you will visit Colchani, the main plant for the iodisation of salt and the best place to observe the methods of salt extraction from the salar. Here ovens are used to dry the salt, which is then formed into cakes. Here you can also purchase handicrafts made of salt. You will continue to the San Cristobal Church, Ollague Volcano viewpoint and finally the Hedionda Lagoon, famous for its various species of white and pink flamingos.</p><p>Tonight you will stay in a desert hotel.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Salt Flats Excursion</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>56</day1><day2>56</day2><destfrom>San Pedro de Atacama</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Enjoy breakfast before visiting the famous stone tree, a unique formation caused by years of erosion from the wind. Continuing on, you will arrive at Laguna Colorada, famous for its red/pink hues and abundance of flamingos. This landscape is perfect for photography lovers.</p><p>The next stop is a little more relaxing - the hot springs of Polques where you can sit back and bathe in the middle of the desert! After some re-charging you will continue onto the green lagoon where you can marvel at the impressive emerald colour.</p><p>Transfer to your accommodation in San Pedro de Atacama and enjoy an evening at your leisure.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>57</day1><day2>57</day2><destfrom>San Pedro de Atacama &amp; Moon Valley</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today you will visit two very impressive highlights of Bolivia - the Tatio Geysers and the Moon Valley. The best time to experience the geysers is very early, so you will be collected at 4am from your hotel. At 4,300 metres above sea level, the fumaroles can easily reach around 10 meters high with the water reaching around eight! Between the soaring peaks, clear sky at sunrise and rising steam, the landscape here is truly breathtaking and worth the early wake up call.</p><p>Next you will visit another natural phenomenon - the Moon Valley. The region is famous for its stone formations and landscape that eerily resembles that of the moon. Your guide will explain how the landscape and climate here has resulted in this unique area.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Tatio Geysers &amp; Moon Valley Excursions</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>58</day1><day2>58</day2><destfrom>San Pedro de Atacama</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>This morning you are free for a much deserved lie in! This afternoon you will be collected for a trip to the Cejar salt lagoons before enjoying an evening of stargazing.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><