 that was once home to the creme de la creme of Chilean society. Also known as The Garden City, Vina del Mar has a host of beautiful parks and beaches.</p><p>Return to Santiago and enjoy the rest of the afternoon at your leisure.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>62</day1><day2>62</day2><destfrom>Santiago</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today you are free to relax and soak up the sights of Santiago. Speak to your Tailormade Specialist about the host of activities you can enjoy today, from bike tours to wine tastings.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>63</day1><day2>63</day2><destfrom>Mendoza</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Transfer to the airport and fly to Mendoza. Laying in the shadow of the Andes, this picturesque city is famous for its incredible wine valleys.</p><p>The city is a mix of charming plazas, tree lined avenues and of course lively wine bars. After check in you are free to start exploring.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Vina del Mar &amp; Valparaiso Tour</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>64</day1><day2>64</day2><destfrom>Mendoza City Tour</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>You will be collected for a city tour of Mendoza. First up your guide will take you to the center of the Foundation - the place where the city was founded by Pedro del Castillo in 1561. This spot was the commercial centre of the city until its destruction in 1861 after an earthquake. The ruins of the San Francisco Church can also still be seen here.</p><p>Next you will visit other important landmarks in the city including the city centre, Independencia Square, Chile Square and San Martin. Passing by the Civic Centre, you will see the Government Headquarters, Palace of Justice and the Center of Congresses. Your guide will explain about the politics of the country and its history as you pass these important buildings.</p><p>You will enjoy San Martin Park, where you can see various monuments and the Lake Regata. Finally, you will visit the Virgin of Lourdes before returning to your accommodation.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Mendoza City Tour</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>65</day1><day2>65</day2><destfrom>Mendoza Wine Cellar Visit</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Enjoy what people come to Mendoza for - the wine tours! You will be taken by your guide to a local wine cellar in Uco valley and enjoy lunch and wine tastings.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Mendoza Wine Cellar Tour</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>66</day1><day2>66</day2><destfrom>Buenos Aires</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Transfer to the airport and fly to your next destination - Buenos Aires!</p><p>The beautiful city of Buenos Aires is known as the "Paris of South America" due to its lovely green parks, plazas and wide boulevards. Explore the quirky neighbourhoods and artistic markets of the city, where European and Latin American influences have mixed together to create a city like no other.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>67</day1><day2>67</day2><destfrom>Buenos Aires City Tour</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>This morning you will explore the highlights of Buenos Aires on a panoramic city tour. Highlights include the Parliament, Pl