 afternoon wandering around the area.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Entrance to Iguazu Falls (Argentinian Side)</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>70</day1><day2>70</day2><destfrom>Puerto Iguazu</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>This morning you will be collected from your hotel for a full day tour of the National Park from the Argentinian side. The Lower Circuit is composed of a trail nearly a mile long that allows you to get close to some of the smaller waterfalls such as the Carlos Bozzetti Waterfall where you can take some great photos. The Upper Circuit allows you to see the top of the majestic falls on the Argentinian side and you can enjoy a breath-taking panoramic view of the area. The view stretches from the Argentinean falls to San Martin Island and parts of the Brazilian falls.</p><p>The Ecological Jungle Train takes you up to the Devil's Throat - the largest waterfall in the region. As you stand at the top of the impressive altitude of 107 metres, you get a feeling of the incredible power unleashed by millions of gallons of water cascading into space. Thanks to the newly built walkway, you can get pretty close to this site. The entrance fee for this excursion is included. Afterwards, you will be transferred to your hotel and the remainder of the day is at your leisure.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Entrance to Iguazu Falls (Brazilian Side)</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>71</day1><day2>71</day2><destfrom>Foz do Iguacu</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today you will experience the Falls from the Brazilian side as you stroll the 1,200 metres of walkways with your private guide on this half-day excursion. Walking along, take in the breath-taking views of the 275 waterfalls from a number of different perspectives. The four main rapids on the Brazilian side are: Floriano, Deodoro, Benjamin Constant and Salto Uni?n or The Devil's Throat.</p><p>As you come to the end of the path, you can hear the roar and see the spray long before you see the water itself. Prepare to get wet, even from a distance, as the spray travels a long way and watch out for the almost permanent rainbow. The entrance fee for this excursion is also included.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>72</day1><day2>72</day2><destfrom>Cuiaba</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>You will be transferred to the airport for your flight to Cuiaba. Upon arrival you will be met by a representative and start the journey to Pantanal North. The first part is a drive along a paved road passing local cattle ranches. The journey continues along 146km of dirt road, passing various flora and fauna of the Pantanal ecosystem. Your driver will stop at some of the best spots of photo opportunities. You will then arrive at your accommodation and be greeted with a welcome drink. The guide will take you on an introductory walk around the lodge and brief you on the next few days.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>73</day1><day2>73</day2><destfrom>Pantanal North</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Enjoy breakfast before taking a photo safari through private dirt roads towards the Clarinho River. You will then board canoes and paddle down the river, taking in the lush surroundings and exploring mangroves. Here lives a colony of giant river otters - if you are lucky you might see a family playing and swimming around!</p><p>You will have the opportunity to try and fish for the elusive piranha - not an easy job but a fun challenge. A 