o and Solumoes rivers. It is the gateway to the Amazon Jungle and has a population of more than 2 million.</p><p>This morning you will be collected for a city tour. Visit the famous Opera House, which was built in 1896 and is a fantastic example of the wealth of the region during the rubber boom. Marble columns from Italy, French mirrors, English ironwork and Portugese stonework - this neoclassical building is a highlight of Manaus and cannot be missed. Your guide will then take you to the harbor and Adolpho Lisboa Municipal Market.</p><p>The rest of the day is at your leisure.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Manaus City Tour</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>80</day1><day2>80</day2><destfrom>Amazon Jungle</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today you will transfer to the port of Manaus and embark your boat, settling into your luxury cabins. Enjoy the sunset as you begin cruising through the Amazon. You will have a welcome meeting and introduction, as well as a briefing for the next few days. Enjoy a cocktail on the deck followed by dinner.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in a jungle lodge . No single room upgrade available.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s), 1 Lunch(es), 1 Dinner(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>81</day1><day2>81</day2><destfrom>Amazon Jungle</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Enjoy breakfast on the upper deck and start taking in the unique atmosphere of the Amazon Jungle. After breakfast you will take a guided walk along some of the walking trails in the jungle, keeping an eye out for the various birds that live here as well as pink river dolphins.</p><p>Next you will visit the home of a local Caboclo, learning all about life in the Amazon and the communities who call it home. You will also have the chance to purchase local handicrafts. Returning to the boat, you will be given a 